<item>
            <title>[SPARK-4772] Accumulators leak memory, both temporarily and permanently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-4772</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Accumulators.localAccums is cleared at the beginning of a task, and not at the end.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that any locally accumulated values hang around until another task is run on that thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If for some reason, the thread dies, said values hang around indefinitely.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is really only a big issue with very large accumulators.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
